#multiple inheritance



class Parent1():
    def string_one(self,str1):
        self.str1=str1
    def show_string_one(self):
        return self.str1
In [93]:
class Parent2():
    def string_two(self,str2):
        self.str2=str2
    def show_string_two(self):
        return self.str2
In [94]:
class Child(Parent1, Parent2):
    def string_three(self,str3):
        self.str3=str3
    def show_string_three(self):
        return self.str3
In [95]:

#SubPlots (multiple plots on single) adding in single outcome

x=np.arange(1,11)
y1=2*x
y2=3*x

plt.subplot(1,2,1)
plt.plot(x,y1, color="y", linestyle=":", linewidth=2)

plt.subplot(1,2,2)
plt.plot(x,y2, color="g", linestyle="-", linewidth=2)
plt.show()
